.START 

Clarcor Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to sell its J.L. Clark unit to a group headed by Anderson Industries Inc. of Rockford for $70.3 million. 

Clarcor said the sale is for cash, notes and an amount to be determined by the company's future performance.
The amount of cash wasn't disclosed. 

The sale of the packaging unit is part of a previously announced corporate restructuring.
The company has said it plans to focus on its filtration and precision products groups. 

Clarcor said it expects to complete the sale of J.L. Clark by Nov. 30. 

